http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/TRS-mandal-unit-chief-supporters-join-YSRC/article13996232.ece

Kusumanchi mandal unit president of the Telangana Rastra Samithi, R. Balakrishna Reddy, and several of his supporters from Palair Assembly constituency, joined the YSR Congress Party (YSRCP).According to sources, Mr. Reddy and more than 300 activists on Tuesday joined the YSRCP in the presence of party Telangana State president and Khammam MP P. Srinivas Reddy at the party district office here.Mr. Reddy had switched over from the Congress to the TRS over a year ago.The reported internal group rivalries among a section of the TRS leaders in Palair Assembly constituency led to his exit from the ruling party, sources added.Meanwhile, talking to newsmen at the YSRCP office here, he said that he joined the YSRCP to strive for fulfilling the ideals of former Chief Minister Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy and further strengthening the party in Khammam district.